10: Sorry, miss. Could I get another cup?
13:
SIR! I've already asked you kindly to
leave me be!
14:
Oh yeah, lady? Sounds like what
you're ASKIN' for is a world of pain!
17: Sounds like it came from over there.
33:
Hmph! You're sorely mistaken if you
think you can afford any of MY
services!
36:
Oh, I'm WELL aware. Which is why I'll
have you and your garish ensemble
fetch a mighty fine price for—
45: Please get your hands off her.
48:
Who the hell're you people? Do you
have any idea who I am?
54:
Suke! Kaku! Do something about
these lowlifes!
65:
Oh, thank you EVER so kindly for
graciously coming to my rescue!
66:
This is ALL on me—so please eat to
your heart's delight, okay?
73:
But we didn't do anything. In fact... I
don't think we even had TIME to do
anything.
77:
Oh, ever so humble! You heard my
cries of distress and came galliantly
to the rescue like true gentlemen!
79:
Not to mention in such outlandish
garb! I've not seen such garish, yet
provocative, designs before!
85:
I figured you weren't from around
these parts. If you don't mind me
asking, have you ever encountered
a place by the name of Hakunroh in
your travels?
98:
We would be glad to assist you,
Miss... er...
101: Oh, dear! Where are my manners?
105: You may call me Kikuno, dearest.
107:
I once worked as an entertainer at
Hakunroh, a parlour of sorts located
in the Hanamachi district of Yamato.
113:
As of now I am but a mere drifter of
sorts—a courtesan without a home.
116:
Ever since that phenomenon five
years ago, both Eastern and
Western Yamato seemingly merged
together, right?
117:
During the event, it was almost as if
Hakunroh had vanished completely
to another world.
120:
I just happened to be outside the
Hanamachi district and managed
to escape. Ever since, I've been
searching for my old home's
whereabouts.
121:
However, I haven't found even a
single clue!
122:
Which is why I'm now seeking your
help.
123:
But it appears that you're unfamiliar
with this place. Please forget I ever
said anything.
128:
We may not be familiar with this
Hakunroh, but we are familiar with
the Kaleidoscope—and this
definitely sounds related.
132:
Indeed. It is very possible that
Yamato of the West has been
warped to another world.
136:
Suizen and the others were
originally from Yamato too, right?
Why don't we take a quick flip and
find out?
139:
Even with the correct coordinates,
I'm unsure if the World Flipper is able
to take us to Western Yamato.
147:
Come with us if you wish to find out,
Miss Kikuno.
153:
Oh dear... Where have you taken
me? Is this... am I in heaven?
156:
Not quite. This is Starview Village—a
nexus to observe worlds from afar.
159:
Is that... Is that floating ball
supposed to be our world?
162:
Without much information to go on,
we'll likely need to travel through
many worlds. Is that okay?
167:
Of course! To be honest, I'm not sure
I quite understand what's going on
here, but I'm prepared to do
anything!
175: I think... that's enough... for one day...
179:
And we've got nothin' to show for it
either.
184: I'm sorry we weren't able to find it...
190:
No, not at all! I just wish I had been
able to provide some more help!
192:
This is more progress than I ever
could have imagined making all on
my own! Just hearing your stories
was enough motivation for me!
194:
And not to mention this "World
Flipper" of yours...
196:
Would it be all right with you all if I
stayed here while I continued my
search?
197:
I would love to try searching with
this... "World Flipper" again!
200:
Of course. Feel free to use it at your
discretion.
202:
How mighty generous of you! Thank
you so much!
207:
Looking forward to having you,
Kikuno.
211:
And I'll earn my keep, dearest—just
leave the... nightly entertainment to
me!
217:
Y-you don't have to do anything like
that here!
